      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_028_4",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Shortly before foreign ministers gathered in Rio, Lula was touring Egypt and Ethiopia. Both had recently joined the BRICS, a group of emerging economies, and Lula was promoting Brazil as a leader for the global south. But it was his inflammatory statements at a press conference in Addis Ababa on February 19th that made headlines. \"What is happening in Gaza and to the Palestinian people has not existed at any other time in history,\" he said, adding erroneously, that \"actually, it has existed: when Hitler decided to kill the Jews\".",
        "bbox": [
          0.06106869992237329,
          0.12351190497526227,
          0.3416030558028175,
          0.2936507934987778
        ],
        "order": 9
      }
    ]
  },
